    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `emmylua_ls`, inlay hints don't show up unless i do `:edit`. Semantic highlight sometimes also doesn't appear.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n`nvim --clean -u repro.lua`:\n```\nvim.lsp.config(\"emmylua_ls\", {\n\tcmd = { \"emmylua_ls\" },\n\tsettings = {\n\t\tLua = {\n\t\t\tworkspace = {\n\t\t\t\tlibrary = { vim.env.VIMRUNTIME },\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t},\n\t},\n\troot_markers = { \".luarc.json\", \".emmyrc.json\", \".luacheckrc\", \".git\" },\n\tworkspace_required = false,\n})\nvim.lsp.enable(\"emmylua_ls\")\n\nvim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable()\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nInlay hints show the first time.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1076+g516363e6ba\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nemmylua_ls 0.12.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux, updated 2025-08-25\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
